C++11
-----

In a few years when C++11 is widely supported ...

1. Use smart pointers (std::unique_ptr) for dynamic memory allocation.
2. Use nullptr instead of NULL (remove <cstdlib> header).
3. PrimeSieve::counts_ should be an std::array.

OpenMP
------

1. Make ParallelPrimeSieve.cpp exception safe once OpenMP supports C++
   exceptions.
2. Once OpenMP supports array reduction I should use it in
   ParallelPrimeSieve.cpp.
